<html>
  <head>
    <&HTML-AND-JAVASCRIPT(.css)>
    <title>Double TAP - Text and Test Anything Protocol</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-body">
        <p class="title">Hello Double TAP</p>
        <p class="subtitle">Text and Test Anything Protocol</p>
        <p class="control">
          Double TAP is lightweight testing framework where users write black box tests as rules
          checking output from tested "boxes". Boxes could be anything from http client, web server
          to messages in syslog. This universal approach allows to test anything with just dropping
          text rules describing system behaviour in black box manner.
        </p>
        <p class="control">
          Follwing a simple example for http web server. <hr>Double TAP code:
          <pre>
          <code>HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Server: gunicorn/19.9.0</code></pre>
          Implementation code (the one producing output):
          <pre><code class="language-bash">curl http://httpbin.org -D - -s -o /deb/null | head</code></pre>
          Test report:
          <pre>[task stdout]
22:39:23 :: HTTP/1.1 200 OK
22:39:23 :: Date: Wed, 31 Dec 2025 19:39:23 GMT
22:39:23 :: Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8
22:39:23 :: Content-Length: 9593
22:39:23 :: Connection: keep-alive
22:39:23 :: Server: gunicorn/19.9.0
22:39:23 :: Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
22:39:23 :: Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true
22:39:23 :: 
[task check]
stdout match &lt;HTTP/1.1 200 OK&gt; True
stdout match &lt;Server: gunicorn/19.9.0&gt; True</pre>
          <hr>
          Double TAP checks are executed via API, given a tested output is in file data.in,
          and desired check is named http-gunicorn:
          <pre><code class="language-bash">curl --data-urlencode "in=@data.in"  --data-urlencode "check=http-gunicorn" http://doubletab.sparrowhub.io/check</code></pre>
          <hr>
          Some more <a href="https://github.com/melezhik/doubletap/tree/main/examples">examples</a> of double tap checks
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
</body>
</html>
